ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The following questions are about how much your parent/guardians know about your life. Please select the first person you would like to talk about for these questions.  This person should be a primary care giver (someone you live with or spend most of you.
Notes: 9= Mother; 10= Father; 11= Grandparent; 12= Aunt; 13= Uncle; 14= Parents significant other; 15= Other; -99= Missing

ElementDescription: How much does your parent/guardians know about: Your choice of friends, who they are, what they are like.
Notes: 1= Very little; 2= A little; 3= Some; 4= A lot; 5= Very much; -99= Missing

ElementDescription: How much does your parent/guardians know about: Your intellectual interests both in and outside school (e.g. reading, playing games).
Notes: 1= Very little; 2= A little; 3= Some; 4= A lot; 5= Very much; -99= Missing
